<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-649-383  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 649 383.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDGE: Work-Group Computing Report  Nov 26 1990 v1 n27 p12(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EDGE Publishing 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>ELF: Groundhog Graphics adds radiation shields to product line.andO;(NoRad product line) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Groundhog Graphics Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Groundhog Graphics NoRad (Computer apparatus) (Productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionOccupational HealthRadiationMonitorsComputer graphics.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Groundhog Graphics, manufacturer of graphics boards, will begin distributionof radiation shields for computer monitors.andM;Doug Sandlin, president of Groundhog, stated, &quot;Our primary customers aregraphics oriented professionals that spend a great deal of time at theirsystems.andP;  There is an increasing amount of concern about the radiation, glareand static electricity that are emitted from monitors, especially amongpeople who use their computers a great deal.&quot;andM;He continued, &quot;After carefully reviewing scientific documentation, compiledby such respected sources as Johns Hopkins University and the KaiserPermanente Medical Group and also conducting extensive market research, wehave determined that radiation shields can be of great benefit to ourcustomers.&quot;andM;Groundhog Graphics will distribute the NoRad brand of radiation shields,citing price/performance ratio as the reason for that selection.andM;Mark Carlson, director of sales and marketing for Groundhog, commented, &quot;TheNoRad shields offer the best protection against electromagnetic radiationavailable, literally 99.99 percent, while extending pricing that is extremelyaggressive.&quot;andM;Sandlin added, &quot;We expect to do very well with this product, but at the sametime, we are offering it to our customers because we believe sincerely thateducation concerning monitor radiation is critical, as is offering anappropriate solution.&quot;andM;The NoRad shields carry a suggested list price of $139, with quantity pricingavailable for both end users and resellers.andM;For further information, contact Groundhog Graphics at 800/GRAPH99, or814/938-8943.andO;</TEXT></DOC>